<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="L" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Livery1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Livery,</orth> subst. 1) delivery, the act of delivering a freehold into the possession of its heir: <cit><quote>to sue his l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.204" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 1, 204</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. r2 2.3.129" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 129</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.3.62" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A IV, 3, 62</bibl>.*<lb />2) a distinguishing dress of servants: <bibl n="shak. lc 195" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 195</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.4.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 4, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 2.2.117" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 2, 117</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 2.2.117" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 2, 117</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mv 2.2.117" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 2, 117</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.5.11" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B V, 5, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.1.80" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 1, 80</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.1.60" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 1, 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.2.17" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 2, 17</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.90" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. V, 2, 90</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 2.3.128" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. II, 3, 128</bibl>.
<lb />3) any particular dress or garb: <emph>never let their</emph> (thy lips') <cit><quote>crimson --es wear,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 506" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 506</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>putting on the destined l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 2.4.138" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 4, 138</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mm 3.1.95" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 95</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.1.70" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 1, 70</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.2.80" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 2, 80</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.5.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. II, 5, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 3.4.10" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 5.3.7" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 7</bibl>.
<lb />4) outward appearance, aspect: <cit><quote>the beauteous l. that he wore,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ven 1107" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 1107</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I give a badge of fame to slander's l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1054" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1054</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>her face wore sorrow's l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 1054" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1054</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>thy youth's proud l.</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 2.3" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 2, 3</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.113" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 1, 113</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 2.1.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 1, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 4.5.106" default="NO" valid="yes">All's IV, 5, 106</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.2.47" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B V, 2, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 2.2.8" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. II, 2, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.4.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 4, 32</bibl>.*<bibl n="shak. ham 3.4.164" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 4, 164</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 4.7.80" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 7, 80</bibl>.
